subproject.description: The overall objective of the full project, implemented by UNEP and UNDP, is to rapidly phase-out all non-exempted uses of methyl bromide (MB) in five CEIT countries (Bulgaria, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland) and provide support to two countries (Azerbaijan and Uzbekistan) to comply with the Montreal Protocol.
subproject.gender code: No noticeable contribution to gender equality
subproject.title: Methyl Bromide Phase Out

title: PIMS 3233 OZ FP: Ozone Methyl Bromide phase out
